  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had to walk from our dais where we sat to report the testimony, which was just to the left of the witness box, and to the right of the prosecuting attorneys and all of their desks, and the translators and the-- the prosecution team, the lawyers, and to the left of the pris-- of the German defense counsel, who were all seated in about three rows, as I remember, in front of the prisoner's dock.",
      "word_count": 77
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And out, and the guard-- in that case, the American MPs on the inside of the courtroom, opened the door.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I picked up my coat, walked down a long hall to-- a cold hall-- to our office, where I had a typewriter-- as we each did, each of the reporters-- and immediately sat down and typed that half hour of transcript.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were told not to worry about making corrections if we made mistakes typing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "These were manual typewriters.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That all we were to do was X out the mistake and start the word again and, you know, hope to get it right the second time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was a very tight operation, as soon as we had that turn.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then we had a schedule so we could-- we-- we knew when we were due back in that courtroom again, you know, for the entire day and the days to come.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Working on that transcript.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not with all of our reporters In that office, the 20-plus, and I have the names of every single one of them.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
